<tr><td align="left" class="newsCategory">GeneralNews - <font align="left" class="newsDate">12:33 PM PST</font></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top" class="newsText">From the Dev Corner:<br><br><blockquote>Hello Norrath,<br> <br>In the next update, tentatively scheduled for December 16th, any bards who have used AA points to purchase either Extended Notes 3 or Sionachie's Crescendo will have those abilities removed and the AA points reimbursed.  The abilities are being changed so that they only affect beneficial songs and chants.  The use of these abilities on some AOE and damage songs or Chants was overbalancing, which made this change necessary.  Please be aware that you will be receiving a refund of these AA points and that you cannot save more than 30 points.  So if your refund brings you over 30, you will need to spend them before you zone after the update.</blockquote>Plan accordingly!</td></tr>
